Robert G. Steele Jr.
Founder, Grandfather Legacy (GFL)

Robert is a 40-year veteran of automation and technical operations, with a career spanning critical infrastructure and high-availability systems. Formerly with Cox Communications, he specialized in intensive troubleshooting and system resilience—the kind of "all-nighter" operational experience that defines industrial-grade stability.

Today, Robert is applying those decades of hardware and automation expertise to the world of Decentralized Science (DeSci). As the architect behind Grandfather Legacy, he is bridging the gap between theoretical physics (The Casimir Effect) and autonomous AI infrastructure.

His vision is the creation of "Zero-Human Companies"—fully autonomous, AI-driven entities that manage complex physical simulations and decentralized assets with the same precision and reliability as a traditional power grid or telecommunications hub.
